/************************EXAMPLE****************************/
/***********************************************************/
/*********************Consistency Checking******************/


1/ What is this example doing ?

This example shows the incremental consistency checking of the agent's Knowledge Base.
It is an adapted version of the "IncrementalConsistencyExample" distributed with Pellet.

Two agents:
- SendPropertyAgent
- VerifyAgent

"SendPropertyAgent" sends a property to verify agent which tries to add it in its Knowledge Base. 
As the received property is inconsistent with "VerifyAgent"'s Knowledge Base, the property is not added and
explanations of inconsistency are displayed.

Watch the output window to see why the sent property is inconsistent with the Knowledge Base.

Files :
SendProperty
- Config File : config/SendPropertyAgent.properties
- Behaviour : memory_init/SendPropertyBehaviour.swrl

VerifyAgent
- Config File : config/VerifyAgent.properties
- Behaviour : memory_init/VerifyBehaviour.swrl


2/ How to run this example
startVerify.bat (Windows)
startVerify.sh (Linux)

